<h1>About This Project</h1>

<p>This Rails project uses data from multiple sources to manage information about dog breeds, individual dogs, and their owners. The goal is to integrate these datasets into a relational database that can be navigated, searched, and displayed in the web application.</p>
</div>

<h2>Datasets Used</h2>

<ul>
  <li>
    <strong>Dog CEO API</strong> — Provides a list of dog breeds and sub-breeds, along with random images for each breed. This data populates the <code>breeds</code> table's <code>image_url</code> column. API documentation is available at
    <a href="https://dog.ceo/dog-api/documentation/random" target="_blank">Dog CEO API</a>.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>CSV Dataset</strong> — Contains structured breed information, including country of origin, fur color, height, eye color, common health problems, character traits, and lifespan. These fields are mapped to <code>breeds.name</code>, <code>breeds.description</code>, <code>breeds.temperament</code>, and <code>breeds.life_span</code>. The dataset was obtained from
    <a href="https://www.opendatabay.com/data/ai-ml/cfd7e1fa-3243-4719-bb34-84105960f5a5" target="_blank">Open Data Bay</a>.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Faker</strong> — Generates random owner data such as first name, last name, email, and address. This populates the <code>owners</code> table for testing and simulating realistic relationships between dogs and owners.
  </li>
</ul>

<h2>Database Structure and Relationships</h2>

<p>The database has three main tables:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>breeds</strong> — Columns: <code>name</code>, <code>description</code>, <code>temperament</code>, <code>life_span</code>, <code>image_url</code>.</li>
  <li><strong>owners</strong> — Columns: <code>first_name</code>, <code>last_name</code>, <code>email</code>, <code>address</code>.</li>
  <li><strong>dogs</strong> — Columns: <code>name</code>, <code>image_url</code>, <code>breed_id</code>, <code>owner_id</code>. Each dog belongs to a breed and an owner.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Relationships:</strong></p>

<ul>
  <li>Each <code>Dog</code> belongs to one <code>Breed</code> and one <code>Owner</code> (one-to-many relationships).</li>
  <li>Each <code>Owner</code> can have multiple <code>Dogs</code>.</li>
  <li>Each <code>Breed</code> can have multiple <code>Dogs</code>.</li>
</ul>

<p>This integration allows the application to combine data from multiple sources, providing a comprehensive view of dogs, their breeds, and owners, which can be navigated and displayed on the site.</p>

